128
00:14:14,370 --> 00:14:16,900
(Are we not trying hard enough?)

129
00:14:17,170 --> 00:14:18,620
(I get this question a lot.)

130
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:23,300
(“Does it make my life easier
that I'm the heir of a billionaire?”)

131
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:27,800
(From where I am, of course, I can see
the world from a better vantage.)

132
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:31,800
(But in the end,
I am no better than any of you.)

133
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:33,890
(I also have a lot to prove.)

134
00:14:49,140 --> 00:14:50,500
Don't you think it's a waste?

135
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:53,540
Gambling away everything you earn?

136
00:14:55,610 --> 00:14:57,010
You think it's gonna make you rich?

137
00:14:58,250 --> 00:14:59,250
What about you?

138
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:01,540
Dealing cards
for less than a thousand a day.

139
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:03,100
Think it's gonna make you rich?

140
00:15:46,020 --> 00:15:47,020
(You're here, )

141
00:15:47,340 --> 00:15:48,600
Not to place your bets.

142
00:15:48,940 --> 00:15:50,620
(You're here to be devoured.)

143
00:16:12,130 --> 00:16:13,130
You idiot.

144
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:15,340
I warned you and you're back here.

145
00:16:15,490 --> 00:16:18,800
I can say that other people
don't know any better,

146
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:20,200
but you…

147
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:21,900
You saw it with your own eyes.

148
00:16:22,270 --> 00:16:24,316
You know what that thing is?

149
00:16:24,340 --> 00:16:25,600
You're in a pinch with money?

150
00:16:26,010 --> 00:16:26,520
What?

151
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,500
Is that why you're cooped up here lately?

152
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:29,760
