153
00:16:35,940 --> 00:16:36,940
Hey.

154
00:16:37,970 --> 00:16:38,970
Hey.

155
00:16:39,910 --> 00:16:40,910
Hey!

156
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,200
Stop.

157
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:45,500
Hey! Don't you hear me?

158
00:16:48,620 --> 00:16:49,620
My name is Niran.

159
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:53,700
If you want to call out to someone,
you might wanna ask for their name.

160
00:16:54,070 --> 00:16:55,200
All this “hey, hey, hey,”

161
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:57,040
I could have thought
you were calling a dog.

162
00:16:57,260 --> 00:16:58,380
Who the hell are you?

163
00:17:00,230 --> 00:17:03,400
Do I look like an old friend of yours?

164
00:17:04,109 --> 00:17:05,109
Hmm?

165
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:08,900
We know each other?

166
00:17:09,030 --> 00:17:09,730
No, jerk.

167
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:10,290
Oh?

168
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:11,599
We don't know each other.

169
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:14,700
But if you're curious,
get behind the wheel.

170
00:17:14,829 --> 00:17:15,400
Hurry up.

171
00:17:15,540 --> 00:17:17,000
I'm tired. I need a nap.

172
00:17:21,589 --> 00:17:22,589
What the hell?

173
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:31,100
We're going to Khao Yai.

174
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,900
Wake me up when we're in Saraburi.

175
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:34,500
My name is Pete.

176
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:45,490
BETONG

177
00:18:40,490 --> 00:18:41,890
You don't play hard to get, do you?

178
00:18:41,950 --> 00:18:43,276
Literally came all the way here with me.

179
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:44,300
Oh.

180
00:19:09,410 --> 00:19:10,540
Hello, Master Niran.

181
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:13,900
Sorry to have to take up your time.

182
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:16,050
It's okay.

183
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:17,230
Show me.

184
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:19,200
This way.

185
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,500
This house is roughly 10 years old.

186
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:35,050
Grandpa meant for it
to be his retirement home.

187
00:19:36,150 --> 00:19:39,400
Master Pawat was responsible for choosing
the location and the feng shui.

188
00:20:59,510 --> 00:21:00,510
Please stop.

189
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:03,840
Uhh…

190
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:07,000
Grandpa never allows anyone
in his bedroom.

191
00:21:11,030 --> 00:21:12,300
I need to check every room.

192
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:44,600
You said someone was responsible
for the feng shui of this house.

193
00:21:48,580 --> 00:21:49,580
Yes.

194
00:21:50,210 --> 00:21:52,650
Then how come there's something
that's not supposed to be here

195
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,720
right there.

196
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:06,920
You a feng shui master?

197
00:23:08,540 --> 00:23:09,600
What happened?

198
00:23:10,110 --> 00:23:12,040
“What happened?”
Didn't you freaking see that?

199
00:23:12,070 --> 00:23:13,100
No, he didn't.

200
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:15,500
Only we could see it.

201
00:23:23,730 --> 00:23:25,786
What you saw at the gambling house
and what you saw just now

202
00:23:25,810 --> 00:23:26,810
are the same thing.

203
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:29,920
It's called 'yao.'

204
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:43,440
ONE WEEK EARLIER

205
00:24:13,430 --> 00:24:15,000
Are you sure we can trust him, honey?

206
00:24:16,850 --> 00:24:18,610
He was recommended personally
by Mr. Pongsak.

207
00:24:23,990 --> 00:24:25,400
How long has he been like this?

208
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:35,220
He flat lined for the first time
a month ago.

209
00:24:36,910 --> 00:24:39,550
When there are no vital signs,
it usually means the person is dead.

210
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:44,200
But Grandpa's vitals came back
after a few minutes.

211
00:24:46,460 --> 00:24:48,700
We thought it was a miracle at first.

212
00:24:49,610 --> 00:24:52,600
But after a few days, it kept happening.

213
00:24:53,470 --> 00:24:55,900
From then until now,
it's happened more than 10 times.

214
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:02,000
Which means his soul succumbed
to the limit of time,

215
00:25:03,590 --> 00:25:05,400
but his body refuses to.

216
00:25:10,450 --> 00:25:11,450
It's because of yao.

217
00:25:12,770 --> 00:25:13,770
Yao?

218
00:25:14,670 --> 00:25:16,000
If I don't feel like explaining,

219
00:25:16,670 --> 00:25:18,750
I'll tell you it is ghosts, ghouls,
and evil spirits.

220
00:25:20,210 --> 00:25:21,420
But that wouldn't be correct.

221
00:25:23,550 --> 00:25:25,540
There are two mystical forces
in the world.

222
00:25:27,020 --> 00:25:28,340
First is the force of nature.

223
00:25:29,220 --> 00:25:30,900
It is pure and righteous.

224
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:35,100
But yao… it's a different force entirely.

225
00:25:36,450 --> 00:25:38,100
It is born against nature.

226
00:25:39,070 --> 00:25:40,400
In defiance of heaven and earth.

227
00:25:41,870 --> 00:25:43,600
In defiance even of death.

228
00:25:49,350 --> 00:25:52,860
But when was it born? How was it born?

229
00:25:53,150 --> 00:25:56,100
Well, that's the question, isn't it?

230
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,170
I need to see his house.

231
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,180
What house?

232
00:26:07,290 --> 00:26:08,290
My father's house?

233
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:11,000
Yao needs a place to inhabit.

234
00:26:11,890 --> 00:26:13,400
It isn't in this room right now.

235
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,500
Before the tycoon came to the hospital,

236
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:20,800
where else do you think is the only place
an old ailing man would be,

237
00:26:21,470 --> 00:26:22,470
if not at his own home?

238
00:26:22,610 --> 00:26:23,610
No!

239
00:26:24,530 --> 00:26:27,000
We can't just let anyone in Papa's house.

240
00:26:27,610 --> 00:26:31,000
Papa never allows strangers
into his home.

241
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:35,500
But if we know what the cause is,
can't we just deal with it right now?

242
00:26:37,090 --> 00:26:42,100
The only way for me to deal with it
is to locate where it is first.

243
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,700
We'll have to talk about this.

244
00:26:51,180 --> 00:26:54,500
I'll contact you
when we've made a decision.

245
00:27:06,930 --> 00:27:14,930
(Why does the top 1% fated
with more wealth and power than the rest?)

246
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:17,100
THE ANANTARAKARN FAMILY

247
00:27:17,250 --> 00:27:20,570
(Is it pure ambition
and divine intervention?)

248
00:27:20,610 --> 00:27:21,706
BILLIONAIRE GRANDSON CRASHES CAR OFF CLIFF

249
00:27:21,730 --> 00:27:22,980
(Or something more?)

250
00:27:23,010 --> 00:27:24,156
CAR ACCIDENT KILLS FAMOUS HEIR

251
00:27:24,180 --> 00:27:26,180
BILLIONAIRE GRANDSON SUCCUMBS
TO MYSTERIOUS ILLNESS

252
00:27:42,050 --> 00:27:44,600
(Yao… it's a different force entirely.)

253
00:27:46,250 --> 00:27:47,900
It is born against nature.

254
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:50,170
In defiance of heaven and earth.

255
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:53,370
In defiance even of death.

256
00:28:31,580 --> 00:28:32,200
(Hello.)

257
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:34,100
I'm sorry I didn't call sooner.

258
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:36,460
But I can't take this anymore.

259
00:28:36,950 --> 00:28:39,000
(I just can't keep seeing
Grandpa like this.)

260
00:28:39,590 --> 00:28:41,100
What does your family say?

261
00:28:41,300 --> 00:28:42,600
I don't care.

262
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:45,300
I'll let you take a look
at Grandpa's house.

263
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:46,800
But…

264
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,100
Can we go right now?

265
00:28:49,570 --> 00:28:53,130
If we waited till morning, I'm afraid
my uncle would catch on and oppose me.

266
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:56,620
I'm sorry, Mr. Top.
I'm currently working on a different case.

267
00:28:56,730 --> 00:28:57,900
I'll give you 10 million.

268
00:28:58,610 --> 00:28:59,610
Please, Master.

269
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:00,800
(I'm begging you.)

270
00:29:10,810 --> 00:29:11,810
Okay.

271
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:14,000
Send me the location.

272
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:30,440
(What you saw at the gambling house and
what you saw just now are the same thing.)

273
00:29:31,170 --> 00:29:32,200
(It's called 'yao.')

274
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:50,180
We call it 'talisman yao.'

275
00:29:51,020 --> 00:29:56,000
Mr. Tian once performed a ritual
to transfer his own life force into it.

276
00:29:56,750 --> 00:29:59,500
Thus nourished it into maturity and power

277
00:30:00,250 --> 00:30:02,010
which made it into the yao that it is today.

278
00:30:02,730 --> 00:30:06,500
This type of yao
brings its worshipper prosperity.

279
00:30:07,270 --> 00:30:10,900
Give them fortune, graces,
and even longevity.

280
00:30:11,630 --> 00:30:15,500
But a power that defies nature
is never free.

281
00:30:16,610 --> 00:30:18,400
It needs something in return.

282
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:22,890
FOUR DEAD IN FAMOUS FAMILY
HELICOPTER CRASH IN KHAO YAI

283
00:30:23,100 --> 00:30:25,570
That is the reason behind
all the misfortunes

284
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:27,600
that often fall on your family.

285
00:30:30,790 --> 00:30:32,900
I contacted Master Pawat's team
to ask about this.

286
00:30:33,530 --> 00:30:35,810
They insisted that their Master
had nothing to do with it.

287
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,520
It's possible that Grandpa was
the one who put that gourd there.

288
00:30:38,740 --> 00:30:41,060
You believe in this nonsense?

289
00:30:41,410 --> 00:30:42,410
It is true.

290
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:43,330
Brother.

291
00:30:43,450 --> 00:30:44,450
That gourd

292
00:30:45,120 --> 00:30:46,300
I've seen it before.

293
00:30:46,860 --> 00:30:50,290
Long ago, Papa kept it in a shrine
that he was a patron of.

294
00:30:51,030 --> 00:30:54,300
But this is the first time I heard
that he moved it into his bedroom.

295
00:30:56,140 --> 00:30:58,400
A human's life force,
both in their body and spirit,

296
00:30:58,970 --> 00:31:00,900
slowly deteriorates with time.

297
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:02,800
The opposite is true for yao,

298
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:05,210
which only grows stronger with time.

299
00:31:06,930 --> 00:31:09,600
It is possible that
once the tycoon became old,

300
00:31:10,660 --> 00:31:12,800
he fell under its influence.

301
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:15,500
His life is under its control,

302
00:31:16,690 --> 00:31:19,400
and is now tethered
to the world by its power,

303
00:31:20,430 --> 00:31:24,460
even though his time
has long come to an end.

304
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:33,100
What do you think we should do?

305
00:31:37,910 --> 00:31:40,420
Since it is a force born against nature,

306
00:31:41,560 --> 00:31:43,430
it needs to be destroyed.

307
00:31:45,420 --> 00:31:46,700
The thing is…

308
00:31:48,250 --> 00:31:51,100
Once yao's power loosens its grip on him,

309
00:31:52,020 --> 00:31:57,200
the tycoon's fate, and consequently,
the fates of your whole family,

310
00:31:58,810 --> 00:32:00,800
are now once again up to heaven and earth,

311
00:32:01,580 --> 00:32:03,500
leaving no room for further defiance.

312
00:32:09,290 --> 00:32:11,450
We need some time to think.

313
00:32:12,850 --> 00:32:13,850
Hold on.

314
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:15,900
Are you all insane?

315
00:32:19,380 --> 00:32:20,886
Something awful is happening
right in front of your eyes

316
00:32:20,910 --> 00:32:22,660
and you need time to think?

317
00:32:22,950 --> 00:32:23,950
What?

318
00:32:24,430 --> 00:32:26,356
How the hell do you idiots manage
to run your gazillion businesses?

319
00:32:26,380 --> 00:32:27,380
Hey.

320
00:32:27,790 --> 00:32:29,380
Or what? You scared?

321
00:32:29,730 --> 00:32:32,660
Without that damn gourd,
you scared your lot wouldn't still be rich?

322
00:32:33,190 --> 00:32:35,600
You scared to admit that maybe
you're actually incompetent?

323
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:37,896
That you're so incompetent
you need to rely on black magic?

324
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:38,570
You little

325
00:32:38,610 --> 00:32:40,000
I agree with him.

326
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:45,100
If that talisman is the cause of this,
then all we need to do is get rid of it,

327
00:32:45,580 --> 00:32:46,770
not leave it like this.

328
00:32:47,530 --> 00:32:48,220
Listen here, Top.

329
00:32:48,430 --> 00:32:52,220
Don't you realize this total stranger
is belittling the work of your ancestors?

330
00:32:52,330 --> 00:32:55,460
Our family has built this empire
for five generations.

331
00:32:55,620 --> 00:32:58,960
My father became the wealthy man
that he is because of his own effort,

332
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,500
his intelligence and labor!

333
00:33:00,660 --> 00:33:03,180
There is no way
he would turn to black magic

334
00:33:03,430 --> 00:33:06,140
or risk the lives of his own offspring.

335
00:33:06,350 --> 00:33:08,280
How could you even believe him, you jerk?

336
00:33:08,330 --> 00:33:09,240
You little shit!

337
00:33:09,270 --> 00:33:10,890
We sent you abroad for good education

338
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:12,596
only for you to believe
in this stupid nonsense?

339
00:33:12,620 --> 00:33:13,920
Answer me!

340
00:33:13,950 --> 00:33:15,050
Do you believe him? Huh?

341
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:17,670
Answer me, Top!

342
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:19,700
- Enough…
- Do you believe him, Top?

343
00:33:19,730 --> 00:33:20,900
I said that's enough!

344
00:33:29,690 --> 00:33:31,900
Even when I'm right here,

345
00:33:32,140 --> 00:33:34,860
no one cares enough to ask me
what I think about all this.

346
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:39,400
Your father never cared, either.

347
00:33:40,730 --> 00:33:45,200
Even now, none of you does.

348
00:33:46,040 --> 00:33:47,200
No difference.

349
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:56,600
Your father has lived and has caused
too much damage for far too long.

350
00:34:03,020 --> 00:34:05,400
It is time for him to die.

351
00:35:14,910 --> 00:35:16,500
Bring me what's in the trunk.

352
00:35:56,500 --> 00:35:57,500
Papa.

353
00:35:58,480 --> 00:35:59,700
You're home now.

354
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:55,050
Are we really not going to try anymore?

355
00:36:58,670 --> 00:36:59,900
Mama made up her mind.

356
00:37:01,060 --> 00:37:02,450
It is time for him to rest.

357
00:38:00,700 --> 00:38:03,300
Is it… over now?

358
00:38:09,510 --> 00:38:11,000
What do you…

359
00:38:31,250 --> 00:38:33,710
What do you think
you're doing to my belonging?

360
00:38:36,150 --> 00:38:37,150
Papa!

361
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:01,280
You…

362
00:39:14,270 --> 00:39:15,270
Top!

363
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:16,440
Papa!

364
00:39:17,650 --> 00:39:19,610
Papa!

365
00:40:04,680 --> 00:40:05,700
Is the ritual over?

366
00:40:06,470 --> 00:40:07,630
There's one thing left to do.

367
00:40:08,290 --> 00:40:09,800
We have to destroy that gourd.

368
00:40:36,390 --> 00:40:37,700
Give it back to me.

369
00:40:41,580 --> 00:40:42,580
Top, dear!

370
00:40:43,530 --> 00:40:45,530
I said give me back my stuff.

371
00:40:46,570 --> 00:40:47,770
What are you waiting for?

372
00:40:47,810 --> 00:40:49,240
Do what my father said!

373
00:40:49,400 --> 00:40:50,600
That is not your father.

374
00:40:51,140 --> 00:40:52,850
It's yao imitating your father.

375
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:54,980
Then you can all go to hell, assholes!

376
00:40:55,670 --> 00:40:56,670
Okay, okay.

377
00:40:57,150 --> 00:40:58,150
I'll give it back.

378
00:40:58,690 --> 00:41:00,400
Just don't freaking kill my friend.

379
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:01,960
Got it?

380
00:41:26,370 --> 00:41:27,370
Shit!

381
00:41:58,370 --> 00:41:59,400
Just go.

382
00:42:00,870 --> 00:42:04,700
Let karma take its course.

383
00:42:06,580 --> 00:42:08,300
Don't fight your fate anymore.

384
00:42:37,960 --> 00:42:39,660
- No, don't!
- Stop! Stop!

385
00:42:39,730 --> 00:42:40,770
Please, don't hurt my son.

386
00:42:40,800 --> 00:42:41,500
I'm begging you.

387
00:42:41,530 --> 00:42:42,720
Stop.

388
00:42:42,870 --> 00:42:43,870
Please.

389
00:42:44,090 --> 00:42:45,140
Please, don't hurt my son!

390
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,500
- Move!
- Shit!

391
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:27,400
You said we had to destroy it.

392
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:10,600
(Nature gives life to men.)

393
00:44:12,330 --> 00:44:18,800
(It is true that men will always
find a way to defy fate.)

394
00:44:19,880 --> 00:44:22,000
(Some by perseverance.)

395
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:25,500
(Some by seeking evil forces.)

396
00:44:27,180 --> 00:44:32,400
(But in the end, everything reverts
to the natural course of things.)

397
00:44:33,620 --> 00:44:36,500
(That is the rule no one can defy.)

398
00:45:01,020 --> 00:45:02,400
(How come I can see it?)

399
00:45:03,060 --> 00:45:04,900
(Yao, I mean.)

400
00:45:07,460 --> 00:45:08,830
Because you are one of them.

401
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:14,300
The tattoo behind your ear.

402
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:19,800
It is a seal.

403
00:45:22,950 --> 00:45:25,670
Someone performed some kind of ritual
on you as a child, didn't they?

404
00:45:27,730 --> 00:45:30,000
That's how yao inhabits a body.

405
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:34,000
Are you turning 24 this year?

406
00:45:35,310 --> 00:45:36,820
Two cycles of the Chinese Zodiac.

407
00:45:37,530 --> 00:45:40,020
Your fate is at a turning point.

408
00:45:42,250 --> 00:45:43,970
The seal has weakened,

409
00:45:44,490 --> 00:45:46,000
and that allows you to see them.

410
00:46:17,400 --> 00:46:18,500
I need a cigarette.

411
00:46:40,570 --> 00:46:41,930
Didn't take you for a scaredy cat.

412
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:44,640
Are you scared?

413
00:46:45,390 --> 00:46:46,390
No, I'm not.

414
00:46:51,370 --> 00:46:53,460
It wouldn't be wrong to be scared.

415
00:46:55,640 --> 00:46:57,700
You just saw an evil force
with your own eyes.

416
00:46:58,380 --> 00:47:01,090
You don't need to repress your fear
if you are scared.

417
00:47:28,180 --> 00:47:34,300
The evil forces that you've encountered,
felt, and unknowingly absorbed,

418
00:47:35,830 --> 00:47:37,100
transfer them to me.

419
00:47:38,780 --> 00:47:39,410
Uh...

420
00:47:39,460 --> 00:47:41,100
Just transfer them all to me.

421
00:48:25,970 --> 00:48:26,970
Well?

422
00:48:27,990 --> 00:48:29,150
Not scared anymore, are you?

423
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:37,900
You're driving for me tomorrow, too.

424
00:48:38,390 --> 00:48:40,300
And don't worry about a thing.

425
00:48:41,310 --> 00:48:42,620
As long as you're with me,

426
00:48:43,760 --> 00:48:44,820
I'll look after you.

427
00:48:56,560 --> 00:48:58,540
I have to defeat that yao
at the gambling house.

428
00:48:59,950 --> 00:49:01,150
Give me chips for one million.

429
00:49:01,340 --> 00:49:03,260
You need to gamble…

430
00:49:03,370 --> 00:49:04,160
Your soul.

431
00:49:04,270 --> 00:49:07,100
I bet with my life and my soul.

432
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:11,800
All in.

433
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:18,370
My paycheck had better be
more fair than this.

434
00:49:18,480 --> 00:49:19,480
A million.

435
00:49:20,170 --> 00:49:21,170
Deal.
